reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 14, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Dropped Right In To My PC
reviews.reviewText: This was an exact replacement for a few years old Power Spec computer. Everything about it was perfect. I got six years of 24/7 use out of the previous EVGA power supply. Couple of minor changes over the past six years. All the wiring is now black. It certainly was not necessary to have the colors, and the black blends in nicely for those of you with lights inside your computer and windows to look. The connectors with fewer conductors are now a ribbon cable, all black. The cable for the mother board is made up of individual cables, and is sleeved. EVGA is a good manufacturer, and I was pleased to order another after years of good service. And the price is very reasonable. The PC power supply I bought, 15 years ago, was $35. I was expecting a hundred or more, but EVGA isn't gouging, and I appreciate that.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 24, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Saved my computer, so far!
reviews.reviewText: Great working unit! It arrived in one day and slotted in to my PC Build from 2017. Computer powered on and fixed my problem. Couldn't be happier! Since my system is older, the older molex connectors came in handy to power the RGB Fans. That was a nice touch. This system is not a power house, but it will allow me to upgrade my graphics card with an 8 pin power card. Plenty of power to run my system as it is. Probably last another 5 years which is fine by me.Here's the story: 2 weeks ago we had a pretty bad storm and I heard thunder and lightning all night. The next day I was using my desktop computer and all of the sudden it shut itself off. I had to reset the power supply switch before the computer would turn back on. The computer booted and I resumed working. The same thing happened for the next 2 weeks, at least every day or two. Then yesterday I went to start it and the computer wouldn't even power on. I suspected the power supply was the issue. Since replacing it's all back to good, so far! :D

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 21, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars EVGA 100-W1-0600-K1 PSU: I would buy it again!
reviews.reviewText: This EVGA 600W PSU replaced the ULTRA 550W unit that at some point has just stopped turning on.For this replacement, I have expected nothing less than an excellence from such a reputed brand.And it have entirely met my expectations so far - for the quality and solid build, and not the least for its super quiet operation.The installation gave no issues as it has all the standard connectors.So, I love it and recommend to others almost without the reservations, but one : I really miss with the traditional multi-colored wires with this device.Of course, it is important only for advanced users, who need to check some particular voltages on connectors, e.g. on the 24 pin one.This PSU wires are all black and they are grouped in “flat” cables. Honestly, I didn’t find any advantage or disadvantage of it.The only remaining question is this PSU durability. My previous ULTRA served on desktop PC with the liquid cooler for about 7 years.Will EVGA be able to work the same long or longer? To be seen.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 3, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Fácil de instalar
reviews.reviewText: En los materiales se ve que es de calidad fácil de instalar, cables de servicio bien cubiertos muy buena compra la verdad muy contento

Fast/easy install, but then again this isn't my first rodeo.Upgraded the wife's GPU, which in turn required a beefier PSU, so here we are. The install went flawlessly and cables although stiff, were easy to manage/tie up. Would have been nice to have modular plugs for a cleaner install but at this price, beggars can't be choosers. There was more than the required power options, with spare CPU and SATA power cables to be tied up.Overall, a great sturdy and trustworthy product so far. Expect no less from EVGA, to be honest.
